<HEADLINE> Istanbul Explosion Caused by Gas Leak: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Interior Minister Murat
Basesgioglu confirmed here the explosion that killed seven people
in Istanbul Thursday may be caused by gas leak.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted Basesgioglu as
saying that police investigators found no evidence of a
bomb explosion.
</P>
<P>
"The Turkish police made two investigations into the strong
explosion, but found no trace for a bomb explosion," he said.
</P>
<P>
Seven people were killed and 104 others, including 11
foreigners, injured in the strong explosion that ripped through
the crowded Misir market in Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was reportedly caused by a gat container used
for a stove at a food stand in the market.
</P>
<P>
Basesgioglu added the police would continue their investigation
into the incident until get a clear picture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
