<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Defender Gets Two-match Ban after Send-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- FIFA's Disciplinary committee
announced that French defender Laurent Blanc would be banned for two
matches.
</P>
<P>
Blanc was shown the red card in a World Cup semi-final match
against Croatia which France won 2-1.
</P>
<P>
At the 74th minute, Blanc pushed Croatian defender Slaven Bilic
in the face and got the red card.
</P>
<P>
French coach Aime Jacquet said earlier on Thursday he would
appeal to FIFA over the sending-off because he felt it was unfair.
</P>
<P>
But FIFA ruled out any appeal when it announced the sanction on
Blanc.
</P>
<P>
A red card means an automatic suspension of one game, with any
additional sanction up to FIFA's disciplinary committee.
</P>
<P>
Blanc will now miss the World Cup final match as well as the
first qualifying gme for the 2000 European Championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
