<HEADLINE> UN Mission's Copter Shot at in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations observer mission
to Angola said here Thursday that one of its helicopters has been
shot eight times by an unidentified gunman in the northern part
of the country.
</P>
<P>
No casualties, however, were reported in the accident.
</P>
<P>
According to a source from the U.N. mission, the helicopter
was shot at when it was conducting normal flight over Toto in the
northern Uigo Province Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The sniper has not yet been identified.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Toto area has been controlled by the
opposition National Union for Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) since April this year.
</P>
<P>
The event happened when the U.N. helicopter was flying leaders
of Uigo Province and members of the U.N. observer mission to Toto
to pave the way for the reestablishment of local governments.
</P>
<P>
The source said the helicopter immediately returned to Uigo
city, capital of the Province and successfully landed after the
incident. 
</P>
