<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Bomb Attack in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and 21
others injured in a bomb explosion in an Algiers suburb
Thursday morning, the Algerian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a police press release as saying that an
explosive devise was detonated at 8.30 a.m. local time in the Wadi
Knis flea market in the town of Bloizdad.
</P>
<P>
When the bomb exploded, the market was croweded with people on
shopping. Five of the wounded were in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
A number of security and medical personnel were sent to the
scene to conduct investigation and rescue the victims.
</P>
<P>
The cause for the explosion remained unclear and no one has
claimed responsibility, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Over 70,000 people have been killed in Algeria's Islamic
insurgency since 1992, in which Islamic militants are launching a
terror campaign to protest the government's cancellation of the
legislative elections in which the Islamic Salvation Front was set
to win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
