<HEADLINE> Greece's Consumer Price Inflation in June Drops Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Greece's consumer price inflation
decreased from 5.3 percent in May to 5.2 percent in June,
according to figures released by the Greek National Statistics
Service (GNSS) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Inflation increased by 0.3 percent between May and June this
year, compared to a 0.4 percent rise in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The GNSS said that average inflation for the period June 1997
to June 1998 was 5 percent, compared to 6.9 percent in the
previous 12-month period.
</P>
<P>
The GNSS attributed June's inflation figure mainly to a 1.9
percent increase in clothing and footwear, a 1.2 percent rise in
furniture, household items and durable consumer goods and a 0.8
percent reduction in foodstuffs and non-alcoholic drinks. 
</P>
