home in Lagos, the News Agency of Nigeria reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, three of Abiola's sons -- Kola, Deji
and Agboola -- were seen earlier Thursday inspecting part of the
grounds of the Abiola home earmarked for the grave, beside the
tomb of the late politician's first wife Simbiat.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Kola as telling a crowd that had converged
at the home that arrangements were on to give Abiola a befitting
burial.
</P>
<P>
