Muslim himself, should be buried in 24 hours after his death.
</P>
<P>
But his body has been kept for a postmortem examination to
prove whether Abiola did die a natural death, as requested by
some of his relatives.
</P>
<P>
An international team of five pathologists from Britain,
Canada and the United States is expected to arrive here Thursday
night the latest to participate in the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The body of Abiola has reportedly been carried to Lagos where
his family members and supporter believe there are better
facilities.
</P>
<P>
A formal announcement would be made on when Abiola would be
buried after a family meeting, said Kola.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency, Kola also pleaded for
calm and understanding as he said it was a difficult period for
him and the country.
</P>
<P>
Two of Abiola's wives, Bisi and Doyin, were on hand to receive
the numerous sympathizers who came to the home to extend
condolence, the report said.  
