<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E. African Task Force Formed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Task Force on the East African
Community was formed here Thursday to publicise the
Community Draft Treaty for Public Debate and Inputs.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Prime Minister Kintu Musoke officiated at the function
held at the International Conference Center, Radio Uganda
reported.
</P>
<P>
The task force is not an arm of government but an independent
body which will do its work without undue interference from
government, Musoke said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that for the first time the public is being
consulted to contribute to the building of a community that is
people-centered and people-driven.
</P>
<P>
In order to achieve the objectives of the community, people
should promote the balanced and equitable development of the east
African countries, exploit the natural resources prudently and
protect the deteriorating environment.
</P>
<P>
Other steps to be taken include enhancement of the role of
women in social and economic development, promotion of good
governance, peace and good neighborliness and basic
infrastructure within the region, he added.
</P>
<P>
The work of the task force mainly covers organizing panel
discussions, seminars and workshops to solicit and secure inputs
into the Draft Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister urged the members of the task force to
undertake the assignment with zeal and determination so that
people's views can be gathered on time and considered seriously.
</P>
</TEXT>
