<HEADLINE> Greece to Float 15 Percent of National Telecom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Greece would float 15 percent of its
national telecom, Hellenic Telecommunications Organization (OTE),
in Autumn on the Athens and New York stock exchanges, Greece's
National Economy and Finance Minister Yiannos Papantoniou
announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Papantoniou said that OTE would
also issue a bond in international markets and carry out a share
capital rise.
</P>
<P>
Such moves would raise 1 trillion drachmas (about 3.33 billion
U.S. dollars), he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that OTE's ownership status would have to be
changed to allow the acquisition by private buyers of up to 45
percent in the state-run telecom from the current legally ordained
25 percent.
</P>
<P>
OTE has already carried out two floatations on the Athens stock
exchange. 
</P>
