<BODY>
<HEADLINE> LIFFE Extends UK Product Trading Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The LIFFE (London International
Financial Futures and Options Exchange) announced Thursday that
from 20 July it will extend the trading hours of its UK equity
products.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of extending trading hours is to bring the UK
equity products more in line with the underlying cash market, the
LIFFE said.
</P>
<P>
By extending the closing times of its UK FTSE Index contracts,
LIFFE will create a longer overlap with the U.S. equity market,
thereby providing greater cross market trading opportunities for
LIFFE users.
</P>
<P>
The alignment in closing times will also simplify hedging and
trading activity because LIFFE users will no longer be exposed to
price changes in the underlying stocks after the LIFFE close.
</P>
<P>
In addition, following consultation with LIFFE Members, the
Exchange will retain its current opening times of 08.35 hrs for
its FTSE 100 Index futures and options contracts, said Daniel
Hodson, LIFFE's Chief Executive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
