<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Licenses of Taxi Service Providers in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa city
administration Thursday warned that it will revoke licences of
taxi service providers if they go ahead with their strike.
</P>
<P>
Speaking here Thursday at a discussion participated by city
administration officials and taxi-owners and drivers on the
implementation of the newly introduced traffic safety regulation,
Ali Abdo, head of the administration, said taxi service should
resume and continue as usual.
</P>
<P>
Ali said the safety regulation is workable, and that problems
arising in its implementation could be resolved through
discussion.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the participants
complained that they are mistreated by traffic policemen and
employees of the Transport and Communications Bureau of the city
administration.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that taxi service providers went on strike
Wednesday in protest of the new regulation which was in effect
the same day.
</P>
<P>
The Addis Ababa city administration warned Wednesday that it
would take legal measures against strikers if they do not resume
service by Thursday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
