<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa to Encourage Nationals to Invest in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The South African government
would continue encouraging national businessmen to invest in
Ghana, President Nelson Mandela said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We expect South African business to ensure that its
investments in Ghana bring lasting benefits through the transfer
of skills and technology," he told a banquet in honor of visiting
Ghanaian President Jerry Rawlings in Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Mandela said cooperation between South African companies and
Ghana was on the increase, especially in the gold mining and
brewing sectors.
</P>
<P>
"There is no doubt that your visit, with your powerful
delegation, will strengthen and expand relations between our two
countries," South African Press Association quoted Mandela as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday, the two leaders witnessed the signing of
an agreement on the promotion and protection of investments
between their countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
