<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agro-Exporters Association to Be Set up in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan horticultural and
floricultural exporters meeting in the capital Kigali Thursday
decided to form an association known as Rwanda Agro-Exporters
Association.
</P>
<P>
The association, which will be the first of this kind in the
country, has the aim of "promoting the export business and
organizing exporters of horticultural and floricultural
products," according to Evase Nsengima, the head of the newly
formed organization.
</P>
<P>
In the beginning of this year, the government invited to Ronen
ILAN, an internationally reknown Jewish exporter of fruits and
flowers to Rwanda to discuss with local exporters on production
and market mobilization for horticultural and floricultural
products, the Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The businessman promised to work with local exporters, but
advised them to be organized. Thursday's meeting of exporters
was a response to this need.
</P>
<P>
The Rwanda Agro-Exporters Association has committed itself to
defending the rights of members and non-members who work in the
same field as well as to the quality standardization of their
exports and market mobilization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
