<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Inspects Xinjiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI July 10 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin visited
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region over the past five days,
where he said that economic and social development in the region
is significant in the country's 21st century development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang visited Aksu, the Payingholen Mongolian Autonomous
Prefecture, the Hui minority's Changchi Autonomous Prefecture, the
city of Turpan, and the regional capital, Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Qian Qichen, vice-premier of the State Council
and Zeng Qinghong, an alternate member of the Standing Committee
of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee and some local officials, Jiang also inspected a
construction project of the southern Xinjiang Railway which runs
from Turpan in the east to Kashgar in the west.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the Autonomous Region's ethnic groups should
hold the banner of ethnic unity high under the leadership of the
CPC and take full advantage of the region's natural resources to
further promote economic and social progress.
</P>
<P>
He gave full affirmation of the region's reforms and
development drives in recent years, saying that more should be
done to speed up development and to make the region an important
part of China's economic growth in the next century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980710.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Inspects Xinjiang (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang also visited Uygur, Hui, Mongolian, and Kazakh herdsmen
and farm families and said that he was delighted with their
improved standard of living.
</P>
<P>
The proper ethnic policies have provided a base and a guarantee
of unity among the various ethnic groups, he said repeatedly,
calling China's new ethnic policy the best in China's several
thousand-year history, and the country's 56 ethnic groups equal
members of one big family.
</P>
<P>
He said that religious practice has shown that the CPC's
religious policy is correct and that the Party and government
should trust and unite the religious believers and provide a legal
base for religious activities so as to adapt religion to the
socialist society.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that a stable society and politics
are a condition for social and economic progress, and that the
unity of ethnic groups can only be achieved by firmly opposing
national splittism and safeguarding the country's unification.
</P>
<P>
New situations require better quality officials, he went on to
say. Jiang also asked that all officials, especially leading ones,
improve their knowledge and their political stance, carry the
Party's tradition forward, and increase their work at the
grassroots level.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also met with local government representatives, the
People's Liberation Army, armed police, and public security
police, and listened to reports, while encouraging them to
contribute more to the region's development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Urumqi on July 4 after winding up his visit to
Kazakhstan where he attended a meeting of China, Kazakhstan,
Kyrghyzstan, Russia, and Tajikistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
