<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Grants Guinea-Bissau Humanitarian Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission decided
Friday to grant an urgent humanitarian aid worth 1 million ECU
(1.1 million U.S. dollars) to Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
The aid, to be managed by the European Community Humanitarian
Office, will facilitate the aid programs orchestrated by
humanitarian organizations for the displaced people in the African
country.
</P>
<P>
Commission officials said that some 250,000 people fled their
homes from the Guinea-Bissau capital after conflicts broke out on
June 7 and tens of thousands more became displaced in other places
such as the provinces of Mansoa, Bissora, Bafata and Gabu.
</P>
<P>
The European Community Humanitarian Office has opened a special
office in Dakar in neighboring Senegal to closely follow the
development of events in Guinea-Bissau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
