<DOCNO> XIE19980710.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Jobless Rate Unchanged at 8.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Canada's unemployment rate was
unchanged at 8.4 percent for the third consecutive month in June,
Statistics Canada said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Though the jobless rate was unchanged, employment actually
declined by an estimated 36,000, the first significant setback in
18 months.
</P>
<P>
Only a decline in the number of people looking for work in June
kept the jobless rate from rising, the statistics agency noted.
</P>
<P>
The job losses were concentrated among Canadian youths. In
June, youth employment declined by 30,000, with the loss entirely
in full-time employment.
</P>
<P>
The youth jobless rate rose 0.2 percentage points to 15.9
percent in June, after remaining unchanged for three months.
</P>
<P>
And in a reversal of recent job-creation patterns, the number
of people of private sector employees fell by 60,000 in the month
while public sector jobs rose by 38,000, the first big gain this
year.
</P>
<P>
"The increase was concentrated in community services in several
provinces but most notably in British Columbia," the agency said.
</P>
</TEXT>
