<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pirated VCDs And LDs Seized in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, confiscated nearly one
and a half million pirated VCDs and LDs on Monday in the nearby
port of Sanshan, the largest smuggling case of VCDs and LDs in
China.
</P>
<P>
Custom officers discovered the VCDs and LDs packed in 1,540
cardboard boxes hidden under 20 tons of waste plastic that was
being imported by Guangdong's Yueqiao Company.
</P>
<P>
The VCDs and LDs were all made in Hong Kong and contain feature
films and Karaoke programs.
</P>
<P>
The case is still under further investigation by Guangdong
Customs and the local police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
