<HEADLINE> French Soccer Team to Parade Through Champs-Elysee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The French national soccer team will
parade through Paris's main thoroughfare Champs-Elysee at 13:00
Monday afternoon, whatever the result would be the final with
Brazil on Sunday, said the French National Football Association
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city government of Paris will organize two
dancing parties at the Bastille Square and the Tuillerie on July
13 and July 14, the latter falls on the French National Day.
</P>
<P>
Rock and Roll of the 1960s, Brazilian samba and pop music will
be performed on the Bastille by the Citizen's orchestra and
others, while musicians like Jules Nicoli and Claude Bolling will
give their best music in the Tuillerie garden.
</P>
<P>
The World's three greatest tenors, Placido Domingo, Jose
Carreras and Luciano Pavarotti will give a concert Friday evening
at the foot of the Tower Eiffel for the World Cup tournament.
</P>
<P>
Some 12,000 people will attend this extraordinary concert on
the park of Champ-de-Mars which will be transmitted live by the
Mondovision around the world.
</P>
<P>
The program to be performed remains secret until the last minute.
</P>
<P>
President Jacques Chirac will decorate on Saturday former
president of the International Football Federation (FIFA) Joao
Havelange with the "Grand Officer of Legion of Honor" medal.
</P>
</TEXT>
