<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Folk Arts Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A festival of Chinese folk arts
opened today in Hohhot, the capital of China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The Third Chinese Quyi Festival will have some 80 programs with
more than 200 folk artists performing over the next seven
days. Quyi originated some 1,300 years ago and had a sort of
golden period during the Ming and Qing dynasties (1368-1911).
</P>
<P>
There are some 300 forms in China, including ballads, story
telling, comic dialogues, and crosstalk. "Pingshu," or story
telling, and "xiangsheng," or crosstalk, are among the favorites
of ordinary Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Some forms of Quyi are declining in popularity among Chinese
who prefer pop music, karaoke, or the Internet for fun, and some
are on the verge of extinction.
</P>
<P>
"We need to reform and renew Quyi and provide better programs
and teach a new generation of performers," says Liu Lanfang,
executive chairwoman of the Chinese Quyi Artists' Association.
</P>
<P>
The festival is held every five years and is sponsored by the
Artists' Association and the Hohhot city government. It will
include discussions on how to revive the old but largely ignored
art form. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980710.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heroin Toll Up Sharply in Vancouver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Heroin has killed 201 people in
Vancouver city in the past six months, "The Globe and Mail"
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
That's a 37-per-cent increase over the 147 deaths during the same
period last year, statistics for the city coroner's office.
</P>
<P>
"If things keep up at this rate, there may well be over 400
deaths this year," chief coroner Larry Campbell said. The record
is 356 heroin overdose deaths in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Vancouver's heroin-overdose death rate first caused alarm back in
1988 when 39 people died. since 1991, more than 100 people have
overdosed every year.
</P>
<P>
Estimates of vancouver's population of addicts who use multiple
drugs, among them heroin, cocaine and crack cocaine-- range from
10,000 to 15,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
