<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Little Parallel Between Financial Crises of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Mexican Foreign
Minister Rosario Green said here Friday that the current Southeast
Asia economic experience is different from the financial crisis
that affected Mexico years ago.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a lecture organized by Singapore's Institute of
Policy Studies, the Mexican foreign minister said, "I consider it
is very difficult to draw parallelisms" between the two crises,
adding "each situation is unique".
</P>
<P>
"We can not teach others," she said. "Others will have to do
the same."
</P>
<P>
But she emphasized that the Mexican experience made valuable
contributions by prompting international awareness about the role
that the global financial organizations should play in the
prevention of future crisis and ignited the urgent reform of the
traditional mechanisms of financial assistance.
</P>
<P>
She said Mexico experienced a very serious financial downturn
at the end of 1994 and many analysts considered it the first truly
global economic crisis because of its nature, its magnitude and
its possible consequences.
</P>
<P>
By taking full responsibilities of the crisis the Mexican
government recognized that it was facing an emergency from the
outset and reacted expeditiously to avoid the collapse of the
financial and productive structures of the country, she noted.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said Mexico immediately adopted and
implemented a very severe program of economic and financial
adjustments with the purpose of restoring economic stability and
regaining the basis for sustained growth.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, she added, Mexico negotiated an unprecedented
package of external financial support with the U.S. government as
well as international financial institutions such as the IMF and
the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
"Through significant sacrifices and discipline of the Mexican
people," she said, "we were able to turn the corner and restore
economic growth."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
