<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Crashes Under 800 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange (KSE)
100-Index crashed Friday to below the 800 barrier as selling
pressure continued unabated in leading scrips.
</P>
<P>
The KSE 100-Index lost 55.74 points to close at 777.2 Friday as
against the previous trading day's close of 832.94 points,
registering a loss of 13.6 billion rupees (296 million U.S.
dollars) in market capitalization.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that differences between the government and the
Independent Power Producers, talks between the government and the
International Monetary Fund, and the State Bank's decision to stop
supply of U.S. dollars to travelers at the official rate had
adverse effects on the share market.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with heads of stock exchanges last week,
Pakistan's Finance Minister Sartaj Aziz promised a package for the
capital market including the injecting funds by banks in stocks.
</P>
<P>
"People in stock markets are eagerly waiting for the package,"
said the analysts.
</P>
<P>
They added that banks had already put conditions and would only
 buy stocks when they observed some profit. 
</P>
