<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan Flood Death Toll Hits 71 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from floods in
Uzbekistan's Fergana region has hit 71, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a dispatch from Tashkent, the Uzbek capital, the agency said
the flood was caused by massive landslides Wednesday in the high
mountains of neighboring Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
Alisher Atabayev, deputy head of administration of the Fergana
region, blamed the disaster on Kyrgyzstan's meteorological services
for lack of appropriate control over the situation around
mountainous lakes.
</P>
<P>
"If they had informed their Uzbek colleagues of the water
movement in time, the tragedy might have been avoided with people
evacuated beforehand," Tass quoted him as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
