<HEADLINE> Egyptian Health Minister Arrives in Baghdad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Health Minister Ismail
Salam arrived here Friday, leading a delegation of doctors and
representatives from pharmaceutical companies on a week-long visit
to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Salam told reporters upon arrival that his visit to Iraq
reflected the common desire to discuss means of enhancing
bilateral cooperation relations in different spheres.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian minister, a heart surgeon, said he would take part
in operation if allowed. He will open the Iraqi-Egyptian Medical
Week here.
</P>
<P>
The 40-member delegation also includes businessmen of the
medicines and medical appliances industry. Egypt has increased its
export of medicines and medical equipment to Iraq under its
oil-for-food deal with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Iraq is suffering under a crippling economic embargo imposed by
the U.N. since its invasion of Kuwait in 1990. But the
oil-for-food deal made an exception by allowing Baghdad to sell
limited amounts of oil to buy humanitarian supplies.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian delegation was greeted at the airport by Iraqi
Health Minister Umed Medhat Mubarak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
