<HEADLINE> China's Retail Price Index Continues to Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's retail price index
continued to drop in June, according to the State Development
Planning Commission and the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The retail price index last month fell 1.9 percent from May and
3 percent from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The consumer price index edged down 1.8 percent from the
previous month and 1.3 percent on a year-on-year base.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period, the retail price index and the
consumer price index were down by 2.1 percent and 0.3 percent,
respectively from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Only Sichuan Province in southwestern China had an increase of
1.5 percent in its retail price index in the first half of the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
