<HEADLINE> Thuram Thinks French Team of 80's Better </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIs, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Lilian Thuram, who scored twice to
put France in their first ever World Cup final match, said he
thought the French team of the 80's were better.
</P>
<P>
Thuram said the team which included such players like Jean
Tigana, Alain Giresse and Michel Platini were the best ever.
</P>
<P>
The French team reached two World Cup semi-finals and won the
1984 European Championship.
</P>
<P>
"Tigana was my idol and that French team had really great
players. I feel they cannot be compared with the current French
side and that they were better than us," said Thuram.
</P>
<P>
Before the kick-off of the France'98 World Cup finals, Thuram
had tipped Brazil to win their fifth title. But now after the
semi-final match, he changed his opinion.
</P>
<P>
"France will be super-motivated. We will be in the Stade de
France in front of 80,000 people against Brazil," Thuram said.
</P>
<P>
Thuram said:"Everyone knows Brazil is a very good team with
individual players who are very strong. But sometimes it's not a
good thing to give too much respect." 
</P>
</TEXT>
