<HEADLINE> Battling Floodwaters in Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guangzhou, July 10 (Xinhua) -- People's Liberation Army
soldiers, armed police, defense forces, and local people have been
busy fighting the rising floodwaters in south China's Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rains have caused flooding in the Xijiang and Beijiang
rivers in Guangdong since the middle of June and have brought
water levels in many reservoirs up to the danger mark. Some 10
cities have already been hit by floods, and many people's
residences are surrounded by floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government today expressed its gratitude for the
PLA soldiers, police and militiamen involved in the fight and who
have been working night and day to help local rebuild their homes
and get their lives back in shape.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of flood relief work seems to have been
completed, but the provincial government has called on departments
to prepare for other possible flooding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
