<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Index Up But Trade Volume Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Market index
was up this week but total turnover was down as trading in
B-shares, which are for foreign investors, continued to fall.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index opened the week at
1315.28 and ended at 1360.62, up 1.91 percent from last week.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 Index, which is based on 30 blue chip stocks
selected from more than 300 A-Shares, which available for domestic
investors, edged up 2.07 percent to close at 3405.78.
</P>
<P>
Total transactions were down 21 percent to end at 17.5 billion
yuan (2 billion U.S. dollars). Of the 458 stocks listed, 278 rose
and 152 fell.
</P>
<P>
B-share stocks closed at 39.51, down 3.23 percent. The 82
million yuan in turnover was 25 percent more than for last week.
</P>
<P>
Trading in funds stood at 951 million yuan, down 23.9 percent
from last week, and the bond market had 41.9 billion yuan in
trading, down 10 percent from last week. 
</P>
