<HEADLINE> Donations For Southern China's Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Parts of southern China affected
by serious flooding today received the first major disaster
relief, amounting to 10 million yuan (about 1.2 million
U.S. dollars), from the Guangzhou Jockey Club.
</P>
<P>
Many parts of China, mostly south of the Yangtze River, have
reported unusually heavy rainfall and flooding since the beginning
of June.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Jockey Club, which was founded in 1992, is a
member of the China Charity Federation and was the first CCF
member to respond to its June 30 call for donations from its more
than 60 members.
</P>
<P>
The Club asked that half of the donation go to flood-stricken
parts of Guangdong Province, where Guangzhou is located, and the
other half to the neighboring provinces of Hunan, Jiangxi and
Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
A CCF official says that the Club also helped when the city of
Zhangjiakou, southwest of Beijing, was hit by a major earthquake,
and when Qinghai Province, in the Northwest, was hit by a serious
blizzard earlier this year. 
</P>
