<HEADLINE> Reception for 37th Anniversary of Sino-DPRK Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) held a reception
this evening to mark the 37th anniversary of the signing of the
Sino-Korean Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual
Assistance.
</P>
<P>
CPAFFC Vice-President Chen Haosu told those present at the
occasion that friendship and cooperation between China and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea have grown since the treaty
was signed, and that, in view of the present international
circumstances, further development of bilateral relations is in
the interests of the two peoples. It will also help promote peace
and stability on the Korean peninsula and in northeast Asia and in
the world as a whole, he added.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK's ambassador to Chin, Chu Chang Jun, praised the
traditional friendship between the two countries and said he
believes that the Sino-Korean friendship, which was cemented by
blood, will continue to grow. 
