<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Maintains Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of China's
economic powerhouse of Guangdong Province, reported an 11.9 percent
GDP increase in the first half of this year, higher than Beijing,
Shanghai, Tianjin and other major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
The city's GDP amounted to nearly 80 billion yuan during this
period, with primary and secondary industries and the service
sector growing by 4 percent, 10.95 percent and 13.57 percent,
respectively. The city utilized some 1.77 billion US dollars of
overseas investment, up 24.5 percent, according to provincial
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Residents' average annual disposable income reached slightly
over 5,800 yuan, a rise of 13.1 percent over last year. A
remarkable change was seen in housing sales, which stood at nearly
7.1 billion yuan, a rise of 80.6 percent. 
</P>
