<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Holds Second Plenum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen
said here today that the current domestic and international
situation is developing to China's advantage and is favorable to
the preparatory work of the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR).
</P>
<P>
His remarks came at the second plenary meeting of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
held in the Great Hall of the People this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting will examine the work reports submitted
by the Preparatory Committee's four sub-groups, set out tasks and
make arrangement for them, and approve some relevant decisions.
</P>
<P>
Delivering the opening address, Qian, who is also chairman of
the Preparatory Committee, reviewed the progress made by the
committee since it was established in May, and said a solid basis
has been laid for sound and orderly work in the future.
</P>
<P>
He asked each work group to firmly grasp all issues related to
a smooth transition and the establishment of the Macao SAR when
they draw up their working arrangements.
</P>
<P>
He said they must take into consideration major
transition-related issues concerning society in order to keep the
work of the Preparatory Committee in line with Macao's long-term
stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Qian pointed out that this will be a great event for the Macao
people and a smooth transfer of power in Macao and the
establishment of the SAR must be realized. He added that the
Preparatory Committee must fully uphold democracy and extensively
solicit opinions in Macao in order to encourage them to
participate in the preparatory work.
</P>
<P>
He said China is now politically stable, reform is progressing
smoothly, the economy is maintaining rapid and healthy
development, and China's international status is on the
rise. Therefore, the general situation is creating favorable
conditions for the work of the Preparatory Committee, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR has just celebrated its first anniversary,
Qian said, noting that the successful implementation of "one
country, two systems" in Hong Kong has and will further
demonstrate more splendid prospects for the Macao people.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was presided over by Xie Fei, vice-chairman of
the Preparatory Committee, whose members listened to the work
reports of the four groups.
</P>
<P>
Chen Ziying, secretary general of the committee, explained the
various opinions as well as the content of a resolution that will
be considered at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
