<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 228.01
points, or 2.7 percent, to close at 8,205.77 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The retreat followed a 2.26-percent drop on Thursday when the
key Hang Seng Index slipped 195.4 points to end at 8,433.78.
</P>
<P>
On Friday when the market suffered an all-round loss, commerce
and industry shares were hardest hit, plunging 3.71 percent.
