<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Stresses Negotiations in Settling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary-general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), has
reiterated that the conflicts in Guinea Bissau should be solved
through negotiations, and that military intervention could only
be the last choice.
</P>
<P>
Salim made the remarks here on Thursday evening after his
meeting with Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano, the Noticias
newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Senegal's military intervention in Guinea Bissau,
Salim said it is at the invitation of Guinea Bissau President
Joao Vieira in accordance with a bilateral agreement between
Bissau and Dakar.
</P>
<P>
The OAU chief stressed that any solution to the crisis should
be based on the respect for the democratically-elected
institutions in Guinea Bissau.
</P>
<P>
Salim also exchanged views with Chissano on conflicts in
Angola, Ethiopia, Eritrea, the Comoros and Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Salim arrived in Maputo on Wednesday night for a three-day
visit in the country. 
</P>
