<HEADLINE> Air Quality in China's Major Cities Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The air quality of China's 46
large cities improved by a wide margin over the previous week,
according to the latest air quality report released today by the
China Environment Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
From July 3 to July 9, 42 cities enjoyed good or excellent air
quality thanks to the rainfall in many regions of the country, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen cities including Xi'an, Wuhan, Xiamen and Zhuhai had
excellent air quality during the period.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's air quality saw notable improvement, reaching the
excellent level, together with another 28 cities including
Shanghai, Tianjin and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Only four cities -- Guangzhou, Hohhot, Taiyuan and Lanzhou --
had slight air pollution. Guangzhou's major problem was nitrogen
oxide, while the major problem of the other three was suspended
particles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
