<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
lower Friday in Sydney but dealers said it held up remarkably well
in the face of continuing yen weakness.
</P>
<P>
The local currency ended at 61.38 U.S. cents from 61.53 U.S.
cents Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Peter Whitley, foreign exchange manager of Colonial State Bank,
said the Australian unit traded quite independently Friday from
the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
While the local unit appeared to be moving away from the yen a
little, Whitley said the correlation between the two currencies
"remains well over 90 percent."
</P>
<P>
At the close in Sydney Friday, the Australian dollar was at
86.84 Japanese yen from 86.17 Thursday and 1.1221 German marks
from 1.1207 marks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
