<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Academy Awards Fellowships to Local, Overseas Artists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's famous action movie
star Jackie Chan and two other local and overseas artists were
awarded honorary fellowships by the Hong Kong Academy for
Performing Arts (HKAPA) here Friday for their outstanding
contributions to the arts.
</P>
<P>
At the 12th graduation ceremony of the HKAPA held Friday
afternoon, Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) presented certificates of fellowships
to Chan, who is also a famous director and producer of action
movies, Fong Yim-fun, a famous Cantonese opera artist, and Neville
Marriner, a world renowned conductor.
</P>
<P>
Chan's movies have always been box office hits in Hong Kong and
he has successfully established his Chinese Kung Fu hero image
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Fong has a successful performing career and originated a unique
singing style, known as the Fong style, in Cantonese opera.
</P>
<P>
Marriner has twice been honored for his services to music. In
1979 he was made a commander of the Order of the British Empire
and in 1985 he received a knighthood.
</P>
<P>
At Friday's ceremony, bachelor's degree was conferred upon a
total of 74 graduates, including 10 from the School of Dance, 16
from the School of Drama, 13 from the School of Film and
Television, 19 from the School of Music and 16 from the School of
Technical Arts.
</P>
<P>
Another 75 graduates were granted professional diploma,
professional certificate, advanced diploma or advanced certificate
 at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The HKAPA was founded in 1985 and was granted degree-awarding
status in 1992. 
</P>
