resident representative, and Celestine Kabalu, the Ministry of
Finance Permanent Secretary in charge of budget and economic
affairs, Times of Zambia reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia education capacity building project will receive 22
billion Kwacha (11 million U.S. Dollars) and a huge amount of the
money will go to the education of vulnerable children, youth
skills training and vocational training, Kabalu noted.
</P>
<P>
