impoverished families and destitutes who will be offered
scholarships, said the permanent secretary, adding that at least
25,000 children have been targeted in the country.
</P>
<P>
He also disclosed that the private sector development will
benefit 17.6 billion Kwacha (about 8.4 million Dollars) which
will be for export development program.
</P>
<P>
Small and medium scale entrepreneurs will be given loans to
buy machinery, equipment and will be provided with working
capital, and this will in turn create employment.
</P>
<P>
The remaining eight billion Kwacha (four million Dollars) will
go to the Zambia n1tD=911="I9MLUM%=9:P%
!~is an important
element in the fight against HIV/AIDS through infected blood.
