<HEADLINE> 17 Die of Snake Bite in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- At least 17 people have died of
snake bite during the summer season in Rupandehi and Dhanusha
districts of Nepal, press reports here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
In Rupandehi district, western Nepal, seven have succumbed to
snake bite and more than 250 others were wounded, the
government-owned Gorkhapatra daily said.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the death toll could be much higher as detailed
reports from some villages are not available yet.
</P>
<P>
It noted that about 100 people in the district have got
injections against snake poison.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 10 have died in Dhanusha district, central Nepal,
the official RSS news agency said, adding that snakes,
particularly kraits, are reported to have been posing a menace
there.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 others were wounded but they have been treated,
the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
About three or four cases of snake bite are treated every day
at local hospitals, it added.
</P>
<P>
Snakes including cobras pose a serious threat to both human
beings and livestock across the Himalayan kingdom during the
monsoon season which lasts from June to September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
