<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Buy Fire Engines From Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government is
planning to buy three modern fire engines from Indonesia in an
effort to enable the Colombo Fire Services (CFS) to put out fires
more effectively, CFS sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said these vehicles are expected to be deployed in
the CFS by the end of this month and they will help control damage
to property in case of fire.
</P>
<P>
Asked how they could minimize damage to the property by using
the new fire engines, a senior official of the CFS explained that
a fire-dowsing engine called "the Triple Agent" has all three
types of extinguishers -- dry powder, water and foam. Any of
these three agents could be put to use to handle different types
of fires.
</P>
<P>
The Triple Agent is a giant vehicle that could carry up to
3,000 liters of water, 3,000 kilos of dry powder and 300 liters of
foam, the sources said. 
