<HEADLINE> 1,000-year-old Chinese Hemlock Tree Found in Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A giant Chinese hemlock tree was
discovered in Zhongdian County in southwest China's Yunnan
Province during a recent resource survey by local foresty
departments.
</P>
<P>
The tree, thought to be over 1,000 years old, measures 2.8
meters in diameter and stands more than 50 meters high, making it
the king of Chinese hemlock.
</P>
<P>
This still-living specimen is one of the rare species of trees
under state protection. The Chinese hemlock is mostly found in
places 2,800 meters above sea level, forestry experts said.
</P>
<P>
Zhongdian County, located in northwestern Yunnan, has an
average elevation of 3,000 meters, and has long been known as
"Shangrila" because of its beautiful and vast primeval forests,
pastures, plateaus, rivers and lakes. 
</P>
