<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Bank to Issue More Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB)
announced today that it will significantly increase financing for
the housing sector in the second half of this year in a bid to
boost economic growth.
</P>
<P>
"Though the value of new loans for the housing sector was
relatively small in the first half, planned loans in the second
half will be substantially greater," a bank official said today.
</P>
<P>
Bank statistics show that the CCB issued 35.12 billion yuan in
housing development loans in the first six months of this year, up
63 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, loans for individual homebuyers surged 175
percent this year to 5.48 billion yuan for the January-June period.
</P>
<P>
The CCB's value of outstandings loans to the real estate sector
totaled 172.8 billion yuan by the end of June, including 26
billion yuan in loans for individual homebuyers, according to the
bank official.
</P>
<P>
China has set this year's gross domestic product growth rate
goal at eight percent and has targeted the housing sector as a
major growth area essential for attaining this goal.
</P>
<P>
The CCB and other commercial banks have all reacted positively
to the government's economic growth plan by considering granting
more loans to the housing sector.
</P>
<P>
The bank plans to issue a total of 50 billion yuan in loans for
real estate development and 35 billion yuan in loans for
individual homebuyers this year, the bank official said.
</P>
<P>
One of China's four largest state-owned commercial banks, the
CCB is also the country's leading provider of medium- and
long-term bank credit for infrastructure, real estate and national
construction projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
