<HEADLINE> Free-Kick Expert Yet to Prove Himself </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Roberto Carlos, one of the
most famous free-kick experts in the world, said he would not waste
his last chance in the match against France.
</P>
<P>
Carlos has failed to master the new ball being used in the World
Cup finals, instead, he has been criticised by captain Dunga for
missing a bicycle clearance in the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
"I have one last chance and I don't intend to waste it," said
Carlos.
</P>
<P>
Carlos is furious over the ball introduced by adidas for the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
"My secret weapon is the swerve and spin I can put on those
kinds of kicks but the ball is so light it is extremely hard to
curve it in." Carlos said.
</P>
<P>
"But I have been working hard in practice and who knows what
might happen on Sunday." 
</P>
</TEXT>
