<HEADLINE> Hunan to Host Property Rights Fair in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
will host a property rights fair in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province,
on July 22-24.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan Provincial government announced at a recent press
briefing in the southern Chinese city that the fair will offer
property rights for 348 projects, including 287 industrial and 29
infrastructure projects in 14 prefectures, autonomous prefectures
and cities, as well as a number of enterprises directly
administered by the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Hunan's state-owned assets currently stand at 210 billion yuan,
a relatively large proportion of which belongs to inefficient
state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Hunan Party and government officials have listed assets
management as one of the province's key tasks for economic
restructuring over the next five years. They have called for the
successful reorganization of the assets in order to revitalize the
idle assets.
</P>
<P>
The province has drafted wide-ranging preferential policies
governing transactions for property rights, and have invited
businessmen form Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, as well as listed
companies in coastal areas and large conglomerates to attend the
fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
