<HEADLINE> China's First Enterprise to Manufacture ABS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Automotive Brake
System Co. Ltd. has recently completed second-phase construction
of a facility to manufacture anti-lock brake systems (ABS).
</P>
<P>
The construction project was completed at a cost of some 130
million Yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Automotive Group and US-based ITT established the
cooperative venture in 1995 to import advanced technology and
equipment to manufacture floating brakes, anti-lock brake systems
and related equipment for Shanghai Volkswagen Automotive
Co. Ltd. and various other Chinese auto manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Automotive Brake Systems has an annual production
capacity of 300,000 brake sets. The company expects its annual
sales volume to hit 810 million yuan, with profits approaching
15.85 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
