<HEADLINE> Changchun Economic Zone Draws 15 Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the Changchun
Economic and Technological Development Zone, one of the key
foreign investment sites in Northeast China, Thursday in Beijing
inked 15 cooperative projects with a total committed investment of
130 million U.S. dollars, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The joint ventures, with investors from the United States,
Germany, Iran and Taiwan, covered industrial sectors ranging from
food to automobile components.
</P>
<P>
These agreements are especially important now, as investment in
China suffers heavily from Southeast Asia's financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"We adopt practical measures to provide more preferential
policies, except those on a State Level," said Yu Deman, director
of the administrative committee with the Changchun zone of Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
Yu noted that some specific projects can enjoy more favourable
terms like low prices for land leases.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, to the non-producing foreign projects, the zone will
offer an income tax rebate, Yu said.
</P>
<P>
The Changchun zone's strategy is typical among the country's
500 development zones at the state and provincial levels, which
have been tapped as key growth areas for the regional economic
health.  
</P>
</TEXT>
