<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Half-Year Trade Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China reported a foreign trade
surplus of 22.56 billion US dollars in the first half of this
year, according to customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign trade volume totaled 151.4 billion US
dollars in the first six months, up 5.2 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The volume includes 86.98 billion US dollars in exports, up 7.6
percent, and 64.42 billion US dollars in imports, up 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
After export increases in 22 consecutive months, China
experienced its first export drop in May. However, both exports
and imports rebounded in June, when exports rose by 1.6 percent to
15.6 billion US dollars and imports grew 5.3 percent to 11.86
billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
