<HEADLINE> Vietnam Hopes for More Assistance from ADB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam hopes that the Asian
Development Bank (ADB) will provide the country with more loans,
experience and personnel training, Vietnamese leaders said.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Communist Party chief Le Kha Phieu and Prime
Minister Phan Van Khai made the remarks here on Thursday while
meeting with ADB Vice President Bong Suh Lee, the Vietnam News
Agency reported.
</P>
