effective assistance to Vietnam in recent years, reiterated the
country's determination to continue with its renovation.
</P>
<P>
Since the resumption of relations between the two sides in
1993, the ADB, which is Vietnam's third biggest lender after Japan
and the World Bank, has provided 1.3 billion U.S. dollars to the
country in five years, the agency said in the report. 
