<HEADLINE> East China Province Improves Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
recently made public a set of regulations on improving the soft
investment environment in this heavily foreign-invested province,
according to a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
He said that the provincial government has placed great
importance on improving the investment environment, especially the
soft environment. The new regulations are aimed at intensifying
its effort to create a more favorable environment for overseas
investment, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations, all illegal charges imposed on
foreign-funded enterprises by local governments will be
canceled, and no new charges will be put on them within two years.
</P>
<P>
The procedures for examining and approving foreign-funded
projects shall be further simplified, and the local Customs office
will provide all necessary conveniences for the quick flow of
goods.
</P>
<P>
All economic cases concerning foreign-funded enterprises shall
be dealt with in time, and the implementation of the verdicts will
be enhanced, according to the regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
