<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia to Sponsor Nadamu Prairie Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 10 (Xinhua) -- North China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region will host the Nadamu Prairie Tourism Festival
from July 25 to August 20 this year.
</P>
<P>
Nadamu, a Mongolian word meaning entertainment and games, has a
tradition of well over 700 years. The festival will be the eighth
event of its kind since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Festivals are common on the grassland during the summer and
autumn seasons when flowers are in full bloom, the grass is green
and cattle and sheep are thriving.
</P>
<P>
Visitors will be able to attend a grand gala in Siziwang
Banner. The festival will feature horsemanship events, archery and
Mongolian wrestling, visits to the homes of local herdsmen and
Mongolian cuisine.
</P>
<P>
The event will also feature tourism and art programs featuring
local folk customs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
