<HEADLINE> Mongolian Government Urged to Resign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The parliamentary group of the
Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party (MPRP) Thursday submitted a
bill to the Great Hural (parliament) urging the government to
resign.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary group believes that the government's decision
to merge the state-owned Renovation Bank into the private Golomt
Bank not only violated the country's constitution and laws but
also posed threat to national economic security and financial
policies, the local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government's wrong decision has led to a crisis in the
parliament, said the MPRP members.
</P>
<P>
In order to avoid a worse situation, they asked Prime Minister
Tsakhya Elbegdory's government to resign.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hural is expected to make a decision on the matter
soon.
</P>
<P>
The government faced strong opposition from the MPRP after it
decided to allow the two banks to merge on May 27.
</P>
<P>
The MPRP bloc in parliament has since then refused to attend
Great Hural meetings, paralyzing parliament since June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
