<HEADLINE> Houston Beats Detroit in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The defending champion Houston
Comets won their seventh straight game with the biggest victory in
WNBA history by mauling the Detroit Shock 96-66 on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The winning team destroyed the New York Liberty by 25 points on
Wednesday and led this game by as many as 30 points.
</P>
<P>
Kim Perrot scored a career-high 22 points, and Sheryl Swoopes
added 19 ahead of Cynthia Cooper's 14 for Houston, which turned
the game into a laugher midway through the first half with a 21-1
run, holding Detroit without a basket for nearly 11 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Cindy Brown netted 14 points for the helpless Shock, who
dropped their third straight game and had a 6-7 record. Korie
Hlede had 11 points for the losers, who shot 38 percent and 14
turnovers tonight. 
