<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Intelligence Predicts Confrontations Among Jews </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Israeli General Security
Service (GSS) has warned that extremist Jewish groups could
prepare to take violent, including armed, action against other
Jews, local daily Haartz reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In its annual report on the security situation of the country,
GSS said that the confrontations could take place in case of the
further withdrawal of Israeli troops in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Israeli government is currently under pressure from the United
States and the Palestinians to accept an American initiative,
which calls on Israel to hand over 13 percent of the West Bank to
the Palestinians in the second redeployment.
</P>
<P>
The left-wing parties urged the government to make an
immediate resolution on the extent of the further withdrawal,
while the extreme right-wing parties warned that they would
topple the government if the redeployment was implemented.
</P>
<P>
The GSS noted that the confrontations among Jews could take
the form of organized violence against state institutions, against
 political leaders, or conflict between different groups within
Israeli society.
</P>
<P>
In the past, when the GSS's annual assessment did refer to
possible armed Jewish groups, it generally referred to potential
conspiracies to strike at Palestinians as a strategy to stall or
halt peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Now, for the first time in the organization's history, the GSS
report includes warnings of possible armed attacks by Jews on
Jews. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
