<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Academy Not to Design Political Reform Blueprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS) has not been assigned the job of drawing up a plan
to reform China's political structure, an academy spokesman said
here today.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that some overseas newspapers have
reported that the CASS has received the task from the central
government of drawing up plans for political reform, and that some
researchers have already begun working on the program. "The
reports are totally groundless," he said.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that the CASS is carrying out a research program
concerning the improvement of a legal system and democracy in
China, but this has nothing to do with a so-called "political
reform plan."
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the academy has been studying
socialist democracy and the legal system for some time, and among
the newly designed 98 research programs there are such items, but
these are merely academic discussions.
</P>
<P>
He noted that as China's top social science research institute,
the CASS will continue to study these important issues, and its
work has the full backing from the central government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
