<HEADLINE> Stoltenberg Beats His Rival in Fame Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Jason Stoltenberg of
Australian beat his countryman Lleyton Hewitt in straight sets in
the second round of the Hall of Fame tennis championships in
Newport of the United States on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Stoltenberg, 28, hammered Hewitt 6-1, 6-3 to take a sweet
revenge on the 17-year-old teenager, who beat him in the finals of
the Australian men's hardcourt championship early this year.
</P>
<P>
"I used my grass court experience," said Stoltenberg, 35th in
the ATP ratings. "He's a little inexperienced, a little impatient
perhaps."
</P>
<P>
John Van Lottum of the Netherlands, 7th seed, beat American
David Wheaton 7-5, 1-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Sargis Sargsian, the fourth seed, was beaten
by Rainer Schuttler of Germany 6-2, 6-7 (7-0), 6-4. 
