<HEADLINE> Slide in Interbank Lending Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's interbanking market
handled 48.1 billion yuan in transactions on 124 trading days in
the first half of this year, according to statistics from the
China Foreign Exchange Trading System.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show a 388 million yuan daily turnover rate on
average for the period.
</P>
<P>
The continual decline in the lending and borrowing amount has
mainly been attributed to two central bank interest rate
reductions which caused the interbank lending rate to plummet by
6.5 percent monthly, with the June turnover falling to 11.6
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Seven new banks were granted approval to join in interbank
lending and borrowing, with a total of 142 commercial banks and
subsidiary branches holding the right as of June 5.
</P>
<P>
The Jan-June turnover for China's interbank bond trading stood
at 1.5 billion yuan. Some 32.5 billion yuan of repurchased bonds
changed hands, with the daily trading volume averaging 241 million
yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
