<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Population Reaches 46.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yangon, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's population is estimated
to have reached 46.4 million in fiscal 1997-98 ending March,
maintaining an annual growth of about 800,000 or 1.84 percent,
according to the latest report on the country's financial,
economic and social conditions.
</P>
<P>
Of the total estimated 46.4 million, the male population
accounts for 23.04 million or 49.66 percent while the female
represents 23.36 million or 50.34 percent.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that 15.45 million or 33.3 percent of the
population are in the age group under 15, 27.4 million or 59.05
percent in the working-age group of 15-59, and 3.55 million or
7.65 percent in the age group of 60 and above.
</P>
<P>
The population proportion of the working-age group of 15-59
increased from 56.46 percent in 1987-88 to 59.05 percent in
1997-98, and that of the group of 60 and above rose from 6.23
percent to 7.65 percent, while that of the under-15 group declined
from 37.31 percent to 33.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the last 10 years, the dependency ratio has fallen from
77.11 percent to 69.34 percent due to the increase in the
population of the working-age group.
</P>
<P>
The total employment is estimated at 18.36 million in 1997-98
in various sectors, with 11.5 million in agriculture, 1.7 million
in trade and 1.6 million in processing and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
According to an estimation, Myanmar's population is to reach
68.5 million in the year 2020 if the present annual growth rate
of 1.84 percent is maintained.
</P>
<P>
The country's population, which stood at 16 million in 1941 and
35.5 million in 1983, has more than doubled in 42 years.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has drafted a population policy to ensure a rational
ratio between the country's population and area, and laid out
plans, including a children's development project, to guarantee
health and fitness for all families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
