<HEADLINE> Disney Criticized for Scenes of Violence, Sex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Walt Disney Co. was criticized
Thursday by a committee of the Texas Board of Education, which
threatens to sell 45-million-U.S.-dollar Disney stock because the
company's movies are too sexy and violent.
</P>
<P>
"I hope it (sale of Disney stock) sends a message to Miramax
Films (a Disney unit) that the public in this country has had
enough of the violence in these movies. How many more school
shootings do you want? " Board Chairman Jack Christie told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
The education board runs the public school system in Texas and
controls the 17.6 billion U.S. dollar Permanent School Fund, in
which 406,000 shares of Disney stock are held.
</P>
<P>
Christie said he was convinced to sell the Disney stock after
American Family Association showed him clips from the
Miramax-produced black comedy "Pulp Fiction," which included
scenes of murder, drug usage and sadomasochism.
</P>
<P>
The committee's decision is subject to approval by the full
15-member board of education Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
