<HEADLINE> 10 killed in Azores Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed and
100 others injured when an earthquake measuring 5.8 on the Richter
scale struck the mid-Atlantic Portuguese Azores islands Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meteorological department said the quake occurred at 0519
GMT and its epicenter was in the sea some 20 kilometers north of
the Faial Island. Some 1,000 people in Faial, about one-tenth of
the local population, were rendered homeless.
</P>
<P>
A French earthquake research institute said the quake was
measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
Earth tremors regularly strike the volcanic islands of the
Azores. Forty-three people were killed, hundreds injured and more
than 20,000 became homeless when a quake struck the region in
1980. 
</P>
</TEXT>
