<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Ghana's Gateway Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday approved
an interest-free credit of 50 million U.S. dollar equivalent for
the Ghana Trade and Investment Gateway Project.
</P>
<P>
This project will seek to increase the competitiveness of
Ghanaian products in the global market through the reform of the
legislative, regulatory and incentive systems, institutional
strengthening and capacity building, as well as development of
private participation in infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The project will also address the issue of inadequate
infrastructure by supporting the development of Free Trade Zones.
</P>
<P>
"Vision 2020," a long-term development program designed by the
government, seeks to create an environment that actively promotes
the flow of foreign capital and resources, that lowers the cost of
doing business in Ghana and provides infrastructure services of
international quality to investors.
</P>
<P>
This plan aims to develop Ghana into a hub in West Africa for
import, export, storage, assembly, distribution, processing,
manufacturing, and trans-shipment of passengers, goods and
services.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional
lending wing for developing countries. 
</P>
