<HEADLINE> Jones Wins 100 Meters Race at Bislett Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, July 9 (Xinhua) -- American world champion Marion
Jones won the 100 meters race at the Bislett Games Golden League
athletics meeting in Oslo, Norway on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Jones clocked 10.82 seconds on a cool, overcast evening in the
first of the six Golden league meetings to be followed by the
final in Moscow on September 5.
</P>
<P>
Jones is one of 12 athletes remaining in contention for one
million U.S. dollars. The money will be shared among any athletes
who manage to win each of their races in the seven meetings.
</P>
<P>
Jones' time was a meeting record and the fourth fastest in the
world this year.
</P>
<P>
Six times world pole vault champion Sergei Bubka of Ukraine was
an early casualty when he failed to clear his opening height of
5.60 meters.
</P>
<P>
World and Olympic 400 meters champion American Michael Johnson
was edged by Britain's Mark Richardson, who won the event in
44.37 seconds. Briton Iwan Thomas finished second ahead of Johnson
in 44.50. Johnson came in third in 44.58.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Haile Gebrselassie, who improved the world 10,000m
mark in Oslo last year, took the 3,000 meters title with a time of
seven minutes 27.42 seconds.
</P>
<P>
World men's 100m champion Maurice Greene of the United States
was upstaged by Namibia's ace Frank Fredericks who ran in 9.95
seconds for the first place. Greene finished second in 9.96.
</P>
<P>
The men's 1,500m title went to Moroccan Hicham El Guerrouj who
reached the finishing line in three minutes 29.12 seconds.
</P>
<P>
In the men's triple jump, Jonathan Edwards of Britain cleared
18.01 meters for the champion and Russian Denis Kapustin was
second in 17.65. 
</P>
