Assistant Governor Ratakorn Nimwatana has said.
</P>
<P>
The investigation also covered the 56 financial institutions
shut down soon after the devaluation of the baht on July 2 last
year, Ratakorn was quoted by Friday's Nation newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
Ratakorn also disclosed that the Central Bank will initiate a
lawsuit against a former financial executive of a "large"
financial company for authorizing undercollaterized loans.
</P>
<P>
