investigation.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank has already filed several lawsuits against
executives of three failed finance companies. Poor management of
the companies was one of the factors that led to the financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ratakorn said the probe mainly focused on high-profile
executives and big-name financial companies.
</P>
<P>
It was the policy of the Central Bank to assign priority on
the probe against large firms which have a greater impact on the
economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Central Bank Governor Chatumongol Sonakul had
agreed to reassign the bank's staffers who were previously
assigned to supervising the closure of finance firms to assist in
the investigation against former financial executives.
</P>
<P>
The assignment will help speed up efforts to bring the culprits
to court, he said. 
