<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Build One More Union Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will build another union
highway between Nawnghkio and Lashio in the northeastern Shan
state, following the completion of the Lashio-Muse highway in the
north late last year.
</P>
<P>
The official New Light of Myanmar newspaper said Friday that
the Nawnghkio-Lashio road will be renovated and upgraded by a
local private company, the Asia World Co., under a second contract
reached between the company and the Public Works of the Myanmar
Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
The Asia World company started to build the 163-kilometer(km)
Lashio-Muse highway, which runs up to the northern end of the
country towards China's southern city of Ruili in Yunnan province,
in July 1996 under its first contract with the Public Works, and
finished the road in September 1997.
</P>
<P>
The renovation and upgrading of roads in northeastern Myanmar
has facilitated the development of Myanmar's border areas and
boosted its border trade with China.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 1,553 km of
highways were built in Myanmar in the 1997-98 fiscal year which
ended in March, extending the country's highways to a total length
of 29,844 km.
</P>
<P>
The country's transport by road, rail, water and air increased
by 6.6 percent in value in 1997-98 over the previous year, sharing
4.3 percent in the gross domestic product of the year. 
</P>
