<HEADLINE> Pneumonia Deaths Increase in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Pneumonia deaths caused by a cold
spell in Peru have increased recently, the local media reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 144 children under five in the department of Puno
died of pneumonia caused by a sudden change of temperature in a
period up until the last days of June, regional authorities said
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
By Thursday, about 19,000 cases of acute lung infections had
been treated in all the hospitals of the department.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the La Libertad department health body
confirmed that 11 children died of pneumonia in that region.
</P>
<P>
Health authorities recorded 3,440 lung infection cases from
January to June 25, plus 345 documented cases of pneumonia and 11
deaths.
</P>
<P>
The spokesmen said that among the acute respiratory infections,
pneumonia was one of the most serious, since no child could resist
it without appropriate and opportune treatment, and children could
die in a short time.
</P>
<P>
The number of pneumonia victims increased to 34 in the
department of Arequipa, most of them were under five.
</P>
<P>
About 118,000 people were affected by acute respiratory
infections in the department in the first half of the year. Of
these, 4,966 were pneumonia cases.
</P>
<P>
Regional health authorities said that to reduce the incidence
of pneumonia they had distributed medicine, while medical and
auxiliary personnel had been trained to promptly diagnose the
disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
