<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Key Chemical Plant Opens in Jilin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's largest neopentadiene
plant recently entered operations in northeast China's Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
The plant, jointly funded by Germany-based Basf Anilin and
Soda Fabrik, the world largest manufacturer of neopentadiene,
and Jilin Chemistry Co. Ltd., has an annual production capacity
of 15,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Neopentadiene a fine chemical used to produce resin powder
needed in the production of furniture, computer cases, farm
machinery and auto parts.
</P>
<P>
The plant will help fill the increasing demand of neopentadiene
in China and Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
