<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Mount Merapi On Full Alert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Residents around Indonesia's
volcano Mount Merapi in Central Java were on full alert on
Thursday after a super-hot steam cloud gushed from its crater,
local press reports said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Atje Purbawinata, a volcanologist in Yogyakarta, said small
lava flows and tremors had been recorded within the mountain,
pointing to the possibility of an eruption.
</P>
<P>
"People are on the alert. The situation can change very
quickly," he said.
</P>
<P>
Volcanologists monitoring the increased activity within Mount
Merapi said the cloud roared down the western face of its cone for
750 meters on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, a much larger steam cloud flattened a village farther
down the slope, killing 60 inhabitants and severely burning
others.
</P>
<P>
Another volcanologist Radomo Purbo told reporters that lava
flows from Merapi should prompt officials to evacuate local
residents from the area soon.
</P>
<P>
The 2,968-meter mountain, 400 kilometers east of Jakarta, is
the most active of 127 Indonesia volcanoes.
</P>
<P>
The last eruption of Merapi was in January 1997, when more than
8,000 nearby villagers had to be evacuated after the volcano
spewed hot gas, ash and lava. 
</P>
</TEXT>
