<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rains Isolate Hundreds of Nicaraguan Farm Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains and flooding rivers
have isolated about 300 farming families in the past two days in
the west of Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Rainfall in the western zone on Tuesday amounted to 171.3
millimeters, the highest figure yet recorded in this country,
leaving dozens of farming families homeless and destroying
cultivated land. The amount of losses is yet to be calculated.
</P>
<P>
The rains were expected to continue for the next 24 hours
because of an area of low pressure, the Nicaraguan Territorial
Studies Institute said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
