<HEADLINE> Cableway Opens in South China's Xishuangbanna Nature Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A cableway has recently opened for
tourists in a nature reserve in Xishuangbanna, Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The 2,063-meter cableway provides tourists with a panoramic
view of the Wild Elephant Valley Forest Park where grows an
abundance of tropical plants and lives wild elephants.
</P>
<P>
The park, which covers 1,500 hectares and 45 km north of the
prefectural capital of Jinghong, is a major tourist attraction and
a national preserve. 
