<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Investors Show Greater Interest in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Taiwanese investors have shown
increasig interest in Southeast China's Guangzhou city, with total
investment ranking now the second largest among overseas investors
there.
</P>
<P>
According to the municiple government, 1,050 Taiwanese-funded
enterprises have registered by April, with contracted funds
totalling 1.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwanese investors tend not to take on partnerships and
quite a number of them have added new investment or expand
operations to other areas.
</P>
<P>
On average, 300,000 Taiwanese enter or exit the Chinese
mainland through Guangzhou each year, and over 6,000 Taiwanese
businessmen and their families now reside in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
