<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Port of Tianjin Sees Fall in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A slight drop in imports and
exports has been recorded at the port of Tianjin for the first six
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
During this period, imports and exports worth 10.396
billion U.S. dollars passed through Tianjin, a drop of 1.9
percent over the same period last year, according to Tianjin Customs
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Of this figure, 6.47 billion U.S. dollars were exports, a 0.9
percent decline; and 3.93 billion U.S. dollars were imports, a drop
of 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the first half, imports and exports of state-owned
enterprises reached 5.78 billion U.S. dollars, a decrease of 6.9
percent, while those of overseas-funded enterprises amounted to
4.43 billion U.S. dollars, an increase of 3.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The first six months saw 1.84 billion U.S. dollars of trade
to the United States, a 10.9 percent increase. The volumes
to Belgium and Spain rose respectively by 22.4 percent and 38
percent.
</P>
<P>
The first half also reported 1.84 billion U.S. dollars, or a
12.8 percent increase in exports of machinery and electronics
goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
