<BODY>
<HEADLINE> City of Springs to Benefit from Sewage Treatment Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Since June 23, nearly 80 percent of
the polluted water of Daming Lake has been channeled into a sewage
treatment plant in a suburb of Jinan, the capital of east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Situated north of Mount Tai and south of the Yellow River,
Jinan has unique topography which made it known as the "city of
springs." By the Jin Dynasty (1115-1234) the city had reported 72
springs. Daming lake is the convergence of these springs, with
46.7 hectares of water surface.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of Daming Lake said that because of a
lack of sewage treatment facilities, domestic and industrial waste
water was being released into Daming Lake at a rate of 30,000
cubic meters per day.
</P>
<P>
This year, silt was cleared from the lake, and some of the
charm should be restored to the city of springs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
