<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Pledges to Meet This Year's Economic Growth Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, the leading
manufacturing center in China, will work harder to meet this
year's goal of ten percent economic growth, according to Mayor Xu
Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the municipality generated 173.8
billion yuan in gross domestic product (GDP) in the first six
months of this year, up 9.4 percent over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
To attain this year's goal, the city will have to realize an 11
percent economic growth in the last half of this year, explained
Mayor Xu, saying that economic growth may be attained if correct
policies are implemented.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has had an average economic growth of 13 percent over
the past six years. Early this year, the city adjusted its
economic growth for the year to ten percent by taking into account
the worsening macro environment caused by the Asian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ren Shangen, head of the Industrial Economic Research Office of
the Shanghai Municipal Economic Commission, said 156 major
industrial manufacturers should intensify efforts to explore and
increase market shares in order to realize 11 percent economic
growth in the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector was also told to find new ways of
investing and raising funds and intensifying technical progress to
foster new economic powerhouses by developing a group of
industrialized high-tech projects and upgrading pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of fund-raising channels will also be an
important task for the city in the remaining months of this year,
said Xu Xueshi, an official with the Development Center attached
to the Shanghai Municipal Government.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that a joint-stock system, listing of enterprises,
floating bonds, establishing risk investment fund and investment
companies, and increasing mortgage loans for housing should all be
utilized in the search for new investment.
</P>
<P>
In the July-December period this year, the foreign trade sector is
trying to export 1.1 billion U.S. dollars more than it did during
the January-June period by continuing to practice a diverse-market
strategy, with the focus on expanding market in Europe, the United
States, Africa and the Middle East, and to increase the added value
of commodities for export.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Xu Kuangdi also urged various economic departments to
step up the structural adjustment in order to meet the demands of
economic globalization and the rapid growth of the market economy
in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
