<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 700 Mln U.S. Dollar Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday two loans totalling 700 million U.S. dollars to Thailand
for further financial reforms and initiatives to help ease the
adverse social impacts of the economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
First loan of 400 million dollars is provided for economic and
financial adjustment program, which will address the causes of the
crisis and help restructure the country's financial and corporate
sectors while strengthening the competitive foundations of the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of 300 million dollars will be used to support the
Social Investment Project. The project is designed to help protect
the poor and unemployed through employment generation schemes and
the provision of essential social services, such as basic health
AIDS care. The project will also finance two funds to assist local
and community based sub-projects.  
</P>
