<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ghanaian President Asks for Patience for Nigerian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 9 (Xinhua) --The visiting Ghanaian
President Jerry Rawlings said Thursday that he had faith in
Nigerian military leader General Abdulsalam Abubakar and asked
the international community to give him more time.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings, who is on a five-day state visit in South Africa, made
the statement to the South African television.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the government under the leadership of General
Abubakar has very good intentions and they must be given the
necessary support by all of us," Rawlings told South African
Broadcasting Corporation in an exclusive interview.
</P>
<P>
He asked the international community to be patient with
Abubakar.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to make a plea that the international community
should probably give him a little time to see what needs to be
done."
</P>
<P>
He said he had faith in Abubakar and described him as "a very
noble man." 
</P>
</TEXT>
